    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-20T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-20T08:00:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.48A6 Liquor/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Capetown</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Courcy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Capetown</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-20T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 20, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 20—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of July 18, noon, full report on this
                    situation being submitted airmail today.<note n="1" xml:id="d676fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Wine Grower’s Association is conducting violent propaganda
                    campaign against American goods following closing American office. Campaign,
                    though not justified by facts, is obtaining support from deciduous fruit growers
                    and is having harmful effect American trade. It would be very helpful if
                    Department could ascertain from Department of <pb facs="0936" n="856"
                        xml:id="pg_856"/> Agriculture and cable if any revision of BPQ 362<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d676fn2">Bureau of Entomology and Plant Quarantine Order
                        362.</note> along the lines suggested by South African entomologists who
                    were in Washington last October is contemplated. Must discuss situation with
                    Decidious Fruit Exchange Thursday.</p>
                <p>I have no knowledge wine shipments held up here account regulation. Have
                    consistently sent Association copies all liquor regulation[s] received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">De Courcy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
